{{Shrine |Name = Susami Oji Shrine |Image = [[File:Susami-Oji Shrine.jpg|300px]] |Location = {{ill|Wakayama Prefecture|ja|和歌山県}}, {{ill|Nishimuro District|ja|西牟婁郡}}, {{ill|Susami Town|ja|すさみ町}} Susami Yamazaki 2290 |Deity = {{ill|Amaterasu Ōmikami|ja|天照大神}} |Rank = |Founded = {{ill|Tenbun|ja|天文}} 15 (1546) |Main Hall = |Alias = Oji Shrine |Pilgrimage Sites = |Festivals = |Rites = |Map = }} '''Susami Oji Shrine''' (周参見王子神社) is a {{ill|Shinto shrine|ja|神社}} located in {{ill|Susami Town|ja|すさみ町}}, {{ill|Nishimuro District|ja|西牟婁郡}}, {{ill|Wakayama Prefecture|ja|和歌山県}}.
== Overview == The shrine was established in {{ill|Tenbun|ja|天文}} 15 (1546) by Saemon-no-Jō {{ill|Fujihara Shian|ja|藤原氏安}}, the then-lord of Susami.
Fifty-five votive tablets (''ema'') dating from the late {{ill|Edo period|ja|江戸時代}} to the {{ill|Meiji period|ja|明治}} have been preserved. Approximately 60% of these are ship ''ema'', indicating the historical prominence of ship traffic in Susami. These artifacts have been designated as cultural properties of the town and are preserved and displayed at the Museum of History and Folklore located within the shrine grounds.
According to the ''{{ill|Kii Zoku Fudoki|ja|紀伊続風土記}}'', the shrine was originally named "Nyakuichi Oji Gongen Shrine." This indicates that the shrine was established by enshrining deities from {{ill|Kumano|ja|熊野}}, but due to the founding era and circumstances, it is not counted among the {{ill|Kumano Ninety-Nine Oji Shrines|ja|九十九王子}}.
* **Address**: Nishimuro District, Susami Town, Susami Yamazaki 2290 * **Transportation**: Accessible via {{ill|JR Kisei Main Line|ja|紀勢本線}} at {{ill|Susami Station|ja|周参見駅}}
== Susami Municipal Museum of History and Folklore == [[File:Susami Municipal Museum of History and Folklore.jpg|thumb|Susami Municipal Museum of History and Folklore]] Located within the grounds of Susami Oji Shrine, this museum preserves and displays historical and cultural artifacts such as items related to the lifestyle and industries of Susami, ancient documents, and votive tablets from Susami Oji Shrine. The museum is open on Tuesdays and Saturdays from 9 AM to 4 PM. Admission is free.
== Related Topics == * {{ill|Obaji|ja|大辺路}} * {{ill|List of Oji Shrines on the Obaji Route|ja|大辺路の王子社一覧}}
== External Links == * [http://www.town.susami.lg.jp/kyouiku/rekisi/siryokan/ Museum of History and Folklore (Town Board of Education)]
